I don&#x27;t think clojure has triple-quoted strings. Something like<p><pre><code>    &quot;&quot;&quot;
    a
    &quot;&quot;&quot;
</code></pre>
parses as three strings, two of which are empty: &quot;&quot;, &quot;\na\n&quot;, and &quot;&quot;. (Clojure strings are allowed to contain literal newlines.)
